						               													<description>Byzantium is the name given to both the state and the culture of the Hellenic Empire in the middle ages. Both the state and the inhabitants always called themselves Hellenes/Roman, as did most of their neighbors. Western Europeans, who had their own Roman Empire. The eastern Europeans called them Orientals or Greeks (Hellenes). Byzantion was the ancient name of the capital city and Byzantines gives the name of the Empire's capital city, as Constantinople (City of Constantinos the Emperor).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Byzantium is an ancient city in Greece and also a board game of Byzantium's &amp;quot;Pessoi&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;This is an ancient board game from the ancient city of Byzantium with boards depicting the Byzantine era. Byzantium also called the Constantinople. Played with Byzantine Greek era letters for 2-6 players.&amp;#10;Also there are three dice  with the ancient shapes of Byzantium.&amp;#10;Highest roll starts the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Byzantium has the following items:&amp;#10;1. Some Colorful Boards (Grids).&amp;#10;2. Byzantium letters connected with numbers for each player.&amp;#10;3. Three dice with shapes.&amp;#10;4. Other materials.&amp;#10;5. A leaflet with some information for this game along with photos from the Byzantine era.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
